txt.en: 'And she... Shelob or Ungwetári... no name can describe her... she took Celeborn!'
'When I met your daughter Zaudru long ago, the sound of her terrible name haunted my mind.'
'They crawled up all around us, and we tried to repel them, but there were just too many....'
'Stay your blades, Elves. There is something I must say to the beast.'
'I do not know his fate or that of the Gilgalar... and we have too many dead or wounded.'
'Do you understand, Shelob?'
'I don't like the look of this....'
'Have we come so far only to fail at the end of our quest?'
'Those of my kin who survived were trapped in darkness, doomed to die beneath Helegrod.'
'No. Not all is lost... not yet.'
'You will spend the rest of your days blinded and broken beneath these mountains...'
'Ungwetári comes!'
Remmorchant, the Net of Darkness
'Too many dead.'
'Celeborn would not want the sacrifices of the Rangers or the Elves to have been in vain.'
'...and you will remember the name: Atli Spider-bane!'
'You must wield the Gilgalar, my friend. Hold off Ungwetári for as long as you can!'
Slain Ungol-stalker
'Come, friends! The moment is at hand!'
'If ever Ungwetári's hunger might abate, let us hope this is the moment... and that Celeborn is not lost to us.'
'I fear Lord Celeborn was left alive only to lure us deeper into Ungwetári's lair.'
'Can it be?'
Slain Ungol-hatchling
'Let us see this journey to its end, my friend.'
'No... it is too late.'
'Lord Celeborn! Can you hear us?'
'Come along, Atli.'
'Ungwetári hangs in the shadows above... it will not be long before she strikes.'
'DO NOT FEAR! I, ATLI SPIDER-BANE, SHALL FREE YOU!'
'Legolas! Over here!'
'...but he needs our help!'
'Aye, lead on. I've come too far to turn back now.'
'Ha ha! Now that's more like it!'
'Thank you, my friends!'
Slain Ungol-spawner
'TBD'
Ungwetári
You must have completed 'Discovery: Remmorchant, the Net of Darkness' to play this instance.
'By Durin's beard, Shelob's still hanging on!'
Slain Ungol-weaver
'Let us show Ungwetári and her children that the light cannot be vanquished!'
'Oh, no she doesn't!'
Slain Ungol-stinger
'Ungwetári means to flee! We cannot allow her to escape, my friends!'
'Speak if you must, Atli. It is... her end.'
'[placeholder]... we were ambushed!'
